WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.420
 So now we talked about cookies and how the server

00:00:03.420 --> 00:00:05.280
 can set cookies in the browser and how the browser

00:00:05.280 --> 00:00:06.120
 has to give it back.

00:00:06.120 --> 00:00:07.620
 Now we're gonna actually do something useful with it,

00:00:07.620 --> 00:00:09.660
 and that is we're going to build Sessions.

00:00:09.660 --> 00:00:12.260
 And Sessions is a place on the server where we record

00:00:12.260 --> 00:00:15.740
 things like this user, such and so of user has logged in.

00:00:15.740 --> 00:00:17.500
 So let's take a look at this.

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:22.540
 So inside the server, there is some code that we've enabled

00:00:22.540 --> 00:00:24.860
 in Django called SessionMiddleware.

00:00:24.860 --> 00:00:27.140
 And what it basically does is it kind of grabs

00:00:27.140 --> 00:00:31.060
 every incoming request right before it comes in

00:00:31.060 --> 00:00:34.820
 to urls.py and it sort of injects itself

00:00:34.820 --> 00:00:36.940
 before urls.py runs.

00:00:36.940 --> 00:00:39.500
 And what it does is it uses the particular cookie value,

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:42.500
 maybe three E, comes in as a cookie,

00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:45.140
 and then it actually grabs the particular session

00:00:45.140 --> 00:00:47.260
 and associates it with our request.

00:00:47.260 --> 00:00:51.780
 And so by the time you're coming into one of your urls.py,

00:00:51.780 --> 00:00:54.900
 one of your views from urls.py, what you find is

00:00:54.900 --> 00:00:57.820
 the cookies have all been set, the session has been set up.

00:00:57.820 --> 00:01:00.400
 It's made a session if necessary.

00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:02.700
 It's looked up an old session if necessary.

00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:04.900
 And so there's a whole bunch of sessions.

00:01:04.900 --> 00:01:08.300
 And these sessions are stored in the database

00:01:08.300 --> 00:01:11.060
 or on files or other kind of places.

00:01:11.060 --> 00:01:14.200
 And there is pretty much one session object

00:01:14.200 --> 00:01:16.680
 for each distinct browser that's out there.

00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:19.940
 And we look them up by knowing what the cookie value was

00:01:19.940 --> 00:01:21.120
 that we set it.

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:23.020
 And so one of the things that SessionMiddleware does

00:01:23.020 --> 00:01:25.820
 is if it doesn't see a cookie coming in,

00:01:25.820 --> 00:01:29.320
 it actually like, oh, well, I'll pick a large random number

00:01:29.320 --> 00:01:30.820
 and then I'll send the cookie back.

00:01:30.820 --> 00:01:34.180
 I will create a new session and I'll send the cookie back.

00:01:34.180 --> 00:01:35.840
 And then I'll be able to look that session up

00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:39.420
 on all of the future requests.

00:01:39.420 --> 00:01:43.280
 So usually we just go ahead and start sessions

00:01:43.280 --> 00:01:44.300
 when we need a new browser.

00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:45.140
 It's simpler.

00:01:45.140 --> 00:01:47.180
 I mean, you can sort of sometimes delay it

00:01:47.180 --> 00:01:48.580
 to save a little bit of resources.

00:01:48.580 --> 00:01:51.500
 But often for most applications right away,

00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:53.940
 you start using sessions and then later

00:01:53.940 --> 00:01:55.580
 you've logged a person in.

00:01:55.580 --> 00:01:57.320
 You are going to mark each browser

00:01:57.320 --> 00:01:58.780
 with some unique random number.

00:01:58.780 --> 00:02:00.620
 And then when that cookie sent back to us,

00:02:00.620 --> 00:02:02.740
 then we can re-associate the session

00:02:02.740 --> 00:02:04.780
 with the incoming request.

00:02:04.780 --> 00:02:08.200
 So Django Middleware handles the creation, deletion,

00:02:08.200 --> 00:02:10.420
 the inserting of data, the deleting of data,

00:02:10.420 --> 00:02:13.440
 and the updating of data in these sessions.

00:02:13.440 --> 00:02:16.020
 The session identifier is a large random number

00:02:16.020 --> 00:02:17.940
 that we put in a browser cookie.

00:02:17.940 --> 00:02:21.060
 First time we meet a browser and then we store

00:02:21.060 --> 00:02:23.460
 using that same number of bit of data on the server

00:02:23.460 --> 00:02:25.900
 and then later when that cookie comes back in

00:02:25.900 --> 00:02:28.720
 on an upcoming request, we basically look up

00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:31.300
 the session data and then re-associate it with request

00:02:31.300 --> 00:02:35.640
 before we go through urls.py and into our views.

00:02:35.640 --> 00:02:37.860
 So we have to enable this.

00:02:37.860 --> 00:02:42.460
 And if you used Django Admin to create your project,

00:02:42.460 --> 00:02:43.300
 this is already there.

00:02:43.300 --> 00:02:45.580
 You can go ahead and look in your settings.py

00:02:45.580 --> 00:02:46.780
 and you'll see that it's there.

00:02:46.780 --> 00:02:48.380
 And you'll also notice that by now

00:02:48.380 --> 00:02:51.220
 you've probably done a bunch of make migrations

00:02:51.220 --> 00:02:53.780
 and migrates and you see it making a session table.

00:02:53.780 --> 00:02:56.340
 So there's all kind of defaults that are set up

00:02:56.340 --> 00:02:58.940
 so that most of your first Django applications

00:02:58.940 --> 00:03:01.100
 are set up to A, support sessions,

00:03:01.100 --> 00:03:02.980
 and B, store sessions in the database,

00:03:02.980 --> 00:03:07.460
 which is a fine way to go for small to medium sized sites.

00:03:07.460 --> 00:03:09.780
 So like I said, they're gonna be stored in the database.

00:03:09.780 --> 00:03:12.560
 You do this migration and you see that it's creating

00:03:12.560 --> 00:03:14.420
 a sessions table for you

00:03:16.920 --> 00:03:19.920
 in your SQLite, db.sqlite3 database.

00:03:19.920 --> 00:03:23.620
 So here we go.

00:03:23.620 --> 00:03:26.600
 We have, as I said, out there, we've met these browsers,

00:03:26.600 --> 00:03:29.860
 we've made a session object in our database,

00:03:29.860 --> 00:03:32.460
 and we've put a cookie in each one.

00:03:32.460 --> 00:03:34.340
 So there's some kind of a cookie

00:03:34.340 --> 00:03:37.340
 that they're all named the same.

00:03:37.340 --> 00:03:40.700
 So we'll name these cookies session ID or something.

00:03:40.700 --> 00:03:42.700
 And so what we've picked random numbers

00:03:42.700 --> 00:03:44.020
 and we've marked them.

00:03:44.020 --> 00:03:48.180
 And so what happens is, is that a browser comes in,

00:03:48.180 --> 00:03:52.040
 a browser sends a request in

00:03:52.040 --> 00:03:53.900
 and they send their cookie along with it.

00:03:53.900 --> 00:03:57.160
 The Django middleware looks among all the sessions

00:03:57.160 --> 00:04:00.160
 and then connects it up and then it does the request.

00:04:00.160 --> 00:04:03.220
 So there's many browsers, each with a different number,

00:04:03.220 --> 00:04:04.480
 and then there's many sessions,

00:04:04.480 --> 00:04:05.820
 each with a different number.

00:04:05.820 --> 00:04:09.780
 And part of reconnecting is creating it.

00:04:09.780 --> 00:04:12.700
 Now, if we look at this from the point of view

00:04:12.700 --> 00:04:16.120
 of one browser and one session object,

00:04:16.120 --> 00:04:19.180
 one session storage area, you know,

00:04:19.180 --> 00:04:23.640
 at some point we come in and it re-associates the session

00:04:23.640 --> 00:04:25.560
 and we're doing some work and we're writing some stuff

00:04:25.560 --> 00:04:28.140
 into the session and then we respond.

00:04:28.140 --> 00:04:31.680
 We go to another request, we can read what we wrote.

00:04:31.680 --> 00:04:33.140
 So we write stuff into the session,

00:04:33.140 --> 00:04:34.940
 we can read it from another one.

00:04:34.940 --> 00:04:37.960
 And then here we can read that same information.

00:04:37.960 --> 00:04:41.080
 And then here we get a post, we read a bunch of information

00:04:41.080 --> 00:04:43.040
 but we write some more information.

00:04:43.040 --> 00:04:45.340
 And so you can kind of think ultimately,

00:04:45.340 --> 00:04:50.040
 just sort of at some level, relax about all the detail

00:04:50.040 --> 00:04:52.800
 and realize that this session is a variable

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:56.540
 that lasts across many request response cycles.

00:04:56.540 --> 00:05:00.840
 The cookie variable sort of also lasts across

00:05:00.840 --> 00:05:02.640
 many request response cycles.

00:05:02.640 --> 00:05:04.820
 The get and the post data, they vanish.

00:05:04.820 --> 00:05:09.080
 So the get data for each one, you use it

00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:10.960
 and you consume it or you store it in a database

00:05:10.960 --> 00:05:14.160
 but the get data from one request is not available

00:05:14.160 --> 00:05:15.160
 on the next request.

00:05:15.160 --> 00:05:18.300
 So we have to use things like sessions sometimes

00:05:18.300 --> 00:05:20.540
 to store little bits of information

00:05:20.540 --> 00:05:23.100
 so that in a later request we can get it back.

00:05:23.100 --> 00:05:27.540
 So the request object has this little attribute

00:05:27.540 --> 00:05:30.520
 called request session which is basically a dictionary.

00:05:30.520 --> 00:05:33.560
 We can put keys in it, we can delete those keys,

00:05:33.560 --> 00:05:35.980
 we can update those keys, we can call .get

00:05:35.980 --> 00:05:39.080
 and retrieve a key to see if it's there, et cetera, et cetera.

00:05:39.080 --> 00:05:42.740
 And so in a sense, we just take request.session

00:05:42.740 --> 00:05:44.460
 and treat it as a magical dictionary.

00:05:44.460 --> 00:05:47.400
 Now we have to remember that each browser

00:05:47.400 --> 00:05:51.900
 has its own dictionary but when we're in a view function,

00:05:51.900 --> 00:05:53.460
 we're only dealing with one browser

00:05:53.460 --> 00:05:56.240
 and so that session is the one associated with that browser.

00:05:56.240 --> 00:06:00.680
 So it's this persistent interface, persistent data

00:06:00.680 --> 00:06:03.400
 that lasts across all these things.

00:06:03.400 --> 00:06:05.840
 So here's a real tiny view function

00:06:05.840 --> 00:06:09.860
 and you can see in this view function

00:06:09.860 --> 00:06:12.020
 what we're going to do is request.session.

00:06:12.020 --> 00:06:16.060
 This is where request.session is where you see

00:06:16.060 --> 00:06:18.440
 the session data, it's basically a dictionary.

00:06:18.440 --> 00:06:20.700
 So we can say .get, then we have a key

00:06:20.700 --> 00:06:24.060
 and we have zero as the default, num visits is the key,

00:06:24.060 --> 00:06:27.100
 zero is the default value and then we're going to get that

00:06:27.100 --> 00:06:30.240
 and add one to it and then store that

00:06:30.240 --> 00:06:33.240
 and this is kind of like how we do counting.

00:06:33.240 --> 00:06:36.040
 If it's, if we get it, if it was four before,

00:06:36.040 --> 00:06:39.320
 we're going to go to plus one and get to five.

00:06:39.320 --> 00:06:42.080
 If it's not there, we just set it to zero,

00:06:42.080 --> 00:06:42.920
 so we set it to one.

00:06:42.920 --> 00:06:45.800
 So somehow num visits is either one

00:06:45.800 --> 00:06:48.480
 or one more than what was previously there

00:06:48.480 --> 00:06:50.320
 and so then what we see is we see the line

00:06:50.320 --> 00:06:53.040
 that actually just stores it back into the session.

00:06:53.040 --> 00:06:55.840
 That's it, it's a dictionary, it's a magic dictionary.

00:06:55.840 --> 00:06:58.420
 It existed before it came in and we're just going

00:06:58.420 --> 00:07:01.640
 to leave it there and somehow magic things take care of,

00:07:01.640 --> 00:07:04.880
 updating all this stuff and so the other thing

00:07:04.880 --> 00:07:07.040
 that we're going to do is we're going to have this go

00:07:07.040 --> 00:07:10.280
 up by one and if it gets over, we're going over four,

00:07:10.280 --> 00:07:11.280
 then we're going to wipe it out.

00:07:11.280 --> 00:07:16.280
 So this will count one, two, three, four, one, two, three, four.

00:07:16.280 --> 00:07:19.080
 And well actually, yeah, one, two, three, four,

00:07:19.080 --> 00:07:21.840
 one, two, three, four and so this del is just

00:07:21.840 --> 00:07:26.740
 the standard Python syntax to remove a entry from a,

00:07:26.740 --> 00:07:30.320
 to remove an entry from a dictionary

00:07:30.320 --> 00:07:32.600
 and then we just kind of print out the number of visits

00:07:32.600 --> 00:07:36.320
 in our little string and our response.

00:07:36.320 --> 00:07:40.520
 And so if we go, we start, we have no cookie.

00:07:40.520 --> 00:07:43.000
 That means that we also then have no session

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:45.360
 and then we go into the session code

00:07:45.360 --> 00:07:48.700
 and you see that it has set a session cookie, right?

00:07:48.700 --> 00:07:52.400
 So we see a session cookie called sesh ID.

00:07:52.400 --> 00:07:54.400
 It's got an expiration date which is,

00:07:54.400 --> 00:07:58.480
 it's not a expire when the browser goes away session

00:07:58.480 --> 00:08:00.320
 and it's got some big long random number

00:08:00.320 --> 00:08:02.820
 and so that is basically the session ID

00:08:02.820 --> 00:08:05.120
 until we get a new session.

00:08:05.120 --> 00:08:08.560
 And as a side effect of that, we've also stored

00:08:08.560 --> 00:08:11.480
 the value one inside the session in the server

00:08:11.480 --> 00:08:13.160
 and printed it out.

00:08:13.160 --> 00:08:17.320
 So we went, we came in, we established a session.

00:08:17.320 --> 00:08:18.440
 We didn't do any of that, right?

00:08:18.440 --> 00:08:21.720
 If we look at our view here, we didn't establish the session.

00:08:21.720 --> 00:08:23.880
 All we did is grab something out of it

00:08:23.880 --> 00:08:26.080
 and that's because the establishment of the session

00:08:26.080 --> 00:08:28.840
 happens in the middleware that's kind of outside of us

00:08:28.840 --> 00:08:32.640
 and so the middleware happens before our code starts

00:08:32.640 --> 00:08:34.440
 and after our code is done.

00:08:34.440 --> 00:08:37.160
 And so the session stuff is just taken care of

00:08:37.160 --> 00:08:38.380
 when we do that.

00:08:38.380 --> 00:08:42.880
 So view count is one.

00:08:42.880 --> 00:08:46.320
 And then what happens is when we just hit refresh,

00:08:46.320 --> 00:08:49.700
 it's going to send the cookie in for that session ID.

00:08:49.700 --> 00:08:54.700
 It's gonna load up the session that's GJ2233

00:08:54.700 --> 00:08:56.960
 and then our code is gonna add one to that number

00:08:56.960 --> 00:08:58.740
 and store it back into the session

00:08:58.740 --> 00:08:59.800
 and then it's gonna be two.

00:08:59.800 --> 00:09:03.480
 And if we hit refresh, it would say three, four,

00:09:03.480 --> 00:09:05.840
 then it would do a reset and we won.

00:09:05.840 --> 00:09:09.320
 And so in this code, we just kinda say request.session

00:09:09.320 --> 00:09:12.160
 and put stuff in it and read stuff out of it.

00:09:12.160 --> 00:09:16.180
 And the cookie is the thing that looks that up.

00:09:16.180 --> 00:09:17.620
 Now if we wanted to take a look at what's

00:09:17.620 --> 00:09:20.920
 in the session table, it's really just a session

00:09:20.920 --> 00:09:25.920
 and you can see that it gets created by your migrate

00:09:25.920 --> 00:09:27.880
 and your make migrations.

00:09:27.880 --> 00:09:29.860
 So we can go right into the database,

00:09:29.860 --> 00:09:31.460
 we can ask for the tables,

00:09:31.460 --> 00:09:34.440
 we can see the Django underscore session

00:09:34.440 --> 00:09:38.160
 and then we can say select star from Django underscore

00:09:38.160 --> 00:09:42.240
 session and so that will show us the data that's there.

00:09:42.240 --> 00:09:45.800
 And so what we're gonna see is the key,

00:09:45.800 --> 00:09:49.100
 which is that session key and then a time

00:09:49.100 --> 00:09:50.760
 and that's used to expire the session

00:09:50.760 --> 00:09:53.460
 'cause these sessions don't last forever.

00:09:53.460 --> 00:09:56.640
 The Django middleware kinda cleans these up after a while,

00:09:56.640 --> 00:09:59.320
 otherwise you'd have sessions that just lasted

00:09:59.320 --> 00:10:01.360
 forever and ever and ever.

00:10:01.360 --> 00:10:05.440
 And then the actual data is this big long string.

00:10:05.440 --> 00:10:08.640
 So what this is, is this is actually an encoded string.

00:10:08.640 --> 00:10:10.460
 And if you really wanna look at it,

00:10:10.460 --> 00:10:14.460
 it's encoded using a technique called base64.

00:10:14.460 --> 00:10:17.160
 And there's a base64 parsing library.

00:10:17.160 --> 00:10:19.820
 Base64 is a way of taking arbitrary data

00:10:19.820 --> 00:10:22.600
 and encoding it in basically letters

00:10:22.600 --> 00:10:23.920
 and numbers upper and lower case.

00:10:23.920 --> 00:10:27.880
 It's a little less dense, I mean it kind of expands,

00:10:27.880 --> 00:10:29.040
 it's not like a compression,

00:10:29.040 --> 00:10:30.680
 it's the opposite of compression.

00:10:30.680 --> 00:10:36.180
 It expands it but makes, it expands the data

00:10:36.180 --> 00:10:37.920
 when it's encoded into base64,

00:10:37.920 --> 00:10:40.100
 but it also means that then you can store it.

00:10:40.100 --> 00:10:42.020
 You don't have to worry about any special characters

00:10:42.020 --> 00:10:43.960
 'cause sometimes when you're going like pasting

00:10:43.960 --> 00:10:45.600
 single quotes and double quotes mess up,

00:10:45.600 --> 00:10:48.160
 all that kinda stuff, by saying here's this string,

00:10:48.160 --> 00:10:50.120
 I wanna encode it in base64,

00:10:50.120 --> 00:10:53.980
 I basically am guaranteed that there will be no weird,

00:10:53.980 --> 00:10:56.760
 weird characters that will cause some kind of problem

00:10:56.760 --> 00:10:57.880
 farther down the line.

00:10:57.880 --> 00:11:03.440
 So if we take a look at our thing

00:11:03.440 --> 00:11:05.320
 and we grab the little thing

00:11:05.320 --> 00:11:08.000
 that's the base64 encoded variable,

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:12.560
 if you decode this, we're gonna base64 decode it,

00:11:12.560 --> 00:11:14.640
 you see that ultimately it's just kind of like

00:11:14.640 --> 00:11:17.900
 a little key value pair that looks pretty much

00:11:17.900 --> 00:11:18.740
 like a dictionary.

00:11:18.740 --> 00:11:21.000
 It's a serialized version of a dictionary.

00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:25.520
 It's a dictionary that has been put into a serialized form

00:11:25.520 --> 00:11:27.800
 and it's in also JSON format

00:11:27.800 --> 00:11:30.160
 and so we can actually sort of tear this apart

00:11:30.160 --> 00:11:32.720
 and use the JSON library to load it up

00:11:32.720 --> 00:11:35.220
 and see what we've got, so.

00:11:35.220 --> 00:11:37.020
 So that's there.

00:11:37.020 --> 00:11:38.440
 You don't have to worry too much about that,

00:11:38.440 --> 00:11:40.920
 it's just somehow this big long thing

00:11:40.920 --> 00:11:43.000
 is being read and written and read and written

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:44.720
 on every request response cycle

00:11:44.720 --> 00:11:48.560
 that is certainly read on every request response cycle

00:11:48.560 --> 00:11:51.920
 and it's written when you modify the data in the session.

00:11:51.920 --> 00:11:53.800
 So this has been a quick set of lectures.

00:11:53.800 --> 00:11:56.540
 We talked about cookies, a way of marking each browser

00:11:56.540 --> 00:11:59.000
 with a big random number and then sessions

00:11:59.000 --> 00:12:02.200
 which are a bit of data that's stored in a database

00:12:02.200 --> 00:12:04.180
 indexed by that large random number

00:12:04.180 --> 00:12:07.180
 and then each request comes in, we get the cookie back

00:12:07.180 --> 00:12:08.680
 and then we look up the session.

00:12:08.680 --> 00:12:11.920
 The session data, key values, key value pairs,

00:12:11.920 --> 00:12:14.400
 basically a dictionary is all stored in there

00:12:14.400 --> 00:12:15.980
 and so we talked a little bit about

00:12:15.980 --> 00:12:19.120
 how we do request.session in Django

00:12:19.120 --> 00:12:21.760
 to implement, to access session capabilities

00:12:21.760 --> 00:12:23.220
 in our Django applications.

00:12:23.220 --> 00:12:25.800
 (upbeat music)

